				<p class="text-text-muted text-sm">Token bucket counters need shared state. For this tutorial, in-memory storage (a dictionary) keeps things simple. A production version would use Redis, but the storage interface should be pluggable so the swap is easy later. GSD records this as a decision in <code class="text-accent text-xs">.planning/STATE.md</code>.</p>
			</div>
