				<p class="text-text-muted text-sm">Research showed middleware runs before DI. The design: middleware handles the global rate check. Per-route overrides use a different pattern — route decorators that set metadata the middleware reads. This keeps the fast path in middleware while allowing route-level configuration.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface p-5">
				<p class="text-heading font-medium mb-2">What identifies a client?</p>
				<p class="text-text-muted text-sm">Default to client IP from the request. Support a configurable key function so users can identify by API key, user ID, or custom logic. The key function takes a <code class="text-accent text-xs">Request</code> and returns a string.</p>
