				<p class="text-text-muted text-sm">Match the existing middleware style exactly: pure ASGI middleware class, config via <code class="text-accent text-xs">__init__</code> params, added via <code class="text-accent text-xs">app.add_middleware()</code>. Tests follow the <code class="text-accent text-xs">tests/test_middleware_*.py</code> convention. This isn't a style choice — it's a constraint from research.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="text-text mb-6">
			Every one of these decisions came from reading the codebase first. The discuss phase didn't invent patterns — it discovered what FastAPI expects and designed the feature to fit. These decisions are now recorded in <code class="text-accent">.planning/STATE.md</code>, so every plan executes with the same understanding.
