	<!-- Section 6: Plan 1 — Token Bucket -->
	<section class="mb-16">
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-heading mb-4">Plan 1: Token Bucket Algorithm</h2>
		<p class="text-text mb-4">
			GSD executes Plan 1 with a fresh context that reads the plan and the relevant parts of the FastAPI codebase. The token bucket algorithm is straightforward: each client gets a bucket of tokens. Each request consumes one token. Tokens refill at a fixed rate. When the bucket is empty, the request is rejected.
		</p>

		<CodeGroup
			title="fastapi/middleware/ratelimit.py — Token bucket core"
			python={`"""Rate limiting with token bucket algorithm."""

import time
from typing import Protocol


class RateLimitStorage(Protocol):
    """Interface for rate limit state storage."""

    def get_tokens(self, key: str) -> tuple[float, float]:
        """Return (tokens_remaining, last_refill_timestamp)."""
        ...

    def set_tokens(self, key: str, tokens: float, timestamp: float) -> None:
        """Update token count and timestamp for a key."""
        ...


class InMemoryStorage:
    """In-memory token storage. Suitable for single-process apps."""

    def __init__(self) -> None:
        self._buckets: dict[str, tuple[float, float]] = {}

    def get_tokens(self, key: str) -> tuple[float, float]:
        return self._buckets.get(key, (-1.0, 0.0))

    def set_tokens(self, key: str, tokens: float, timestamp: float) -> None:
        self._buckets[key] = (tokens, timestamp)


class TokenBucket:
    """Token bucket rate limiter.

    Args:
        rate: Number of tokens added per second.
        capacity: Maximum tokens in the bucket.
        storage: Where to persist bucket state.
    """

    def __init__(
        self,
        rate: float,
        capacity: int,
        storage: RateLimitStorage | None = None,
    ) -> None:
        self.rate = rate
        self.capacity = capacity
        self.storage = storage or InMemoryStorage()

    def consume(self, key: str) -> tuple[bool, float]:
        """Try to consume a token. Returns (allowed, retry_after_seconds)."""
        now = time.monotonic()
        tokens, last_refill = self.storage.get_tokens(key)

        if tokens < 0:
            # First request — initialize bucket
            tokens = self.capacity - 1
            self.storage.set_tokens(key, tokens, now)
            return True, 0.0

        # Refill tokens based on elapsed time
        elapsed = now - last_refill
        tokens = min(self.capacity, tokens + elapsed * self.rate)

        if tokens >= 1.0:
            tokens -= 1.0
            self.storage.set_tokens(key, tokens, now)
            return True, 0.0

        # Not enough tokens — calculate retry delay
        retry_after = (1.0 - tokens) / self.rate
        self.storage.set_tokens(key, tokens, now)
        return False, retry_after`}
		/>

		<p class="text-text mb-4">
			The <code class="text-accent">RateLimitStorage</code> protocol means the storage is pluggable from day one. The in-memory implementation works for this tutorial; swapping in Redis later means implementing two methods. GSD recorded this decision during the discuss phase.
		</p>
		<p class="text-text mb-4">
			Now the tests — pure logic, no web framework involved:
		</p>

		<CodeGroup
			title="tests/test_ratelimit_core.py — Unit tests"
			python={`import time
from unittest.mock import patch
from fastapi.middleware.ratelimit import TokenBucket, InMemoryStorage


def test_allows_requests_within_capacity():
    bucket = TokenBucket(rate=10.0, capacity=5)
    for _ in range(5):
        allowed, _ = bucket.consume("client-1")
        assert allowed is True


def test_rejects_when_exhausted():
    bucket = TokenBucket(rate=10.0, capacity=2)
    bucket.consume("client-1")
    bucket.consume("client-1")
    allowed, retry_after = bucket.consume("client-1")
    assert allowed is False
    assert retry_after > 0


def test_tokens_refill_over_time():
    bucket = TokenBucket(rate=10.0, capacity=2)
    bucket.consume("client-1")
    bucket.consume("client-1")

    # Simulate time passing
    with patch("time.monotonic", return_value=time.monotonic() + 1.0):
        allowed, _ = bucket.consume("client-1")
        assert allowed is True


def test_separate_keys_have_separate_buckets():
    bucket = TokenBucket(rate=10.0, capacity=1)
    bucket.consume("client-1")
    allowed, _ = bucket.consume("client-2")
    assert allowed is True


def test_retry_after_is_accurate():
    bucket = TokenBucket(rate=1.0, capacity=1)
    bucket.consume("client-1")
    _, retry_after = bucket.consume("client-1")
    assert 0.5 < retry_after <= 1.0


def test_storage_interface():
    storage = InMemoryStorage()
    storage.set_tokens("key", 5.0, 100.0)
    tokens, ts = storage.get_tokens("key")
    assert tokens == 5.0
    assert ts == 100.0`}
		/>

