				<span><strong class="text-heading">Read before you write.</strong> GSD's research phase discovers how the codebase works — its patterns, conventions, and implicit constraints. In an unfamiliar codebase, this research prevents you from building something technically correct but architecturally wrong.</span>
			</li>
			<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
				<span class="text-accent mt-1 shrink-0">&#9656;</span>
				<span><strong class="text-heading">Follow the codebase's patterns, not your own.</strong> The rate limiter uses pure ASGI middleware because that's what FastAPI does. Matching conventions makes your code reviewable, maintainable, and mergeable. GSD records these as constraints during discuss.</span>
			</li>
			<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
				<span class="text-accent mt-1 shrink-0">&#9656;</span>
